-- Brazil economic activity index drops 0.18 pct in May -central bank
-- 
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 07:40AM EDT
-- None



BRASILIA, July 17 (Reuters) - The Brazilian central bank's IBC-Br economic activity index <BRIBC=ECI> dropped 0.18 percent in May from April in seasonally adjusted terms, the bank said on Thursday.

The median estimate in a Reuters survey of 18 analysts was for a 0.5 percent drop.